🛠️ Common Industry-Used Ansible Playbooks-

🔧 1. Server Provisioning & Configuration-

•	Install base packages (curl, git, net-tools)
•	Set hostname, timezone, locale
•	Configure SSH access and firewall rules
•	Harden OS (e.g., disable root login, enforce password policies)

🐳 2. Container & Dev Environment Setup-

•	Install Docker or Podman
•	Setup Docker Compose files
•	Build and run container images
•	Configure registry authentication

☁️ 3. Cloud Infrastructure Provisioning-

•	Create VMs on Azure, AWS, GCP (via Ansible modules or Terraform integration)
•	Configure NICs, storage, and tagging
•	Bootstrap cloud VMs with roles for apps and monitoring

🔄 4. CI/CD Pipeline Preparation-

•	Install Jenkins, GitLab Runner, or GitHub Actions runner
•	Configure Groovy pipeline templates
•	Add required credentials, secrets, or SSH keys

🔐 5. Security Hardening & Patch Management-

•	Apply OS updates (apt/yum/dnf)
•	Install antivirus agents
•	Mitigate vulnerabilities (e.g. CVE-specific patching via vars)
•	Enforce file permissions and auditd rules

📦 6. Software Installation-

•	Automate installation of app stacks (e.g., LAMP/LEMP)
•	Deploy and configure monitoring agents (Prometheus node exporter, Datadog, etc.)
•	Install language runtimes (Python, Java, Node.js)

🧩 7. App Deployment & Configuration-

•	Deploy WAR/JAR/Python apps
•	Update configs via Jinja2 templates
•	Restart/reload services with notify:

📈 8. Monitoring & Logging Setup-

•	Install and configure Prometheus, Grafana, ELK/EFK
•	Setup custom exporters
•	Apply alerting rules and dashboards

🔁 9. Backup & Restore Automation-

•	Schedule backups with cron or systemd timers
•	Push backups to S3, Azure Blob, or remote servers
•	Restore tasks using conditional logic

🖥️ 10. VM Imaging & Golden Image Prep-

•	Preinstall software before snapshot
•	Clean up temp files and SSH keys
•	Convert VMs to templates (especially in VMware/Azure)

🖥️ 10. Shubham Playbook-

•	install_nginx.yml
•	install_docker.yml
